2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
½ tsp Garlic Salt
1 unit(s) Blueberry Jam
2 tbsp BBQ Sauce
1 unit(s) Sweet Potato
170 g Green Beans
2 unit(s) Green Onion
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Butter*
0.06 tsp Salt*

Cut sweet potatoes into 1/4-inch rounds.
Add sweet potatoes and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the bottom of the oven, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden-brown, 20-23 min.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the green onions.
Add Beyond Meat® patties, breadcrumbs, cheddar cheese and half the green onions to a large bowl. Season with 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic salt and pepper, then combine.
Roll mixture into 8 equal-sized meatballs (16 meatballs for 4 ppl).

Arrange meatballs on the parchment-lined baking sheet.
Roast in the middle of the oven until golden-brown and cooked through, 12-14 min.**

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
Trim green beans.
When hot, add green beans and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until water evaporates and beans are tender, 4-5 min.
Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter and remaining green onions. Cook, stirring often, until butter coats green beans and green onions are tender, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and cover to keep warm.

Add blueberry jam and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) water to a small pot.
Heat over medium heat.
Cook, whisking constantly, until jam is smooth and warmed through, 30 sec.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add half the BBQ sauce to the pot (use all for 4 ppl). Cook, whisking occasionally, until well-combined and warmed through, 1 min.
Remove the pan from heat.

Divide sweet potatoes, green beans and meatballs between plates.
Spoon blueberry BBQ sauce over meatballs.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, prepare and cook it the same way the recipe instructs you to prepare and cook the pork.**